No, I'll get it.

00:16:06.000 --> 00:16:07.000
I'll tell him I'll get it.

00:16:07.000 --> 00:16:08.000
And I'll be on the phone.

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:09.000
Okay.

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:10.000
I'm off.

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:11.000
See you around.

00:16:12.000 --> 00:16:13.000
Mr. Ken.

00:16:13.000 --> 00:16:14.000
Sam Phelan.

00:16:14.000 --> 00:16:15.000
Metropolis PD.

00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:16.000
I, uh, figured you'd be the one to show.

00:16:16.000 --> 00:16:17.000
What do you want with my son?

00:16:17.000 --> 00:16:18.000
We're both rational adults.

00:16:18.000 --> 00:16:19.000
Let's sit down.

00:16:19.000 --> 00:16:20.000
Let's talk about this.

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:21.000
I don't think a rational adult drops a generator on top of a teenage boy.

00:16:21.000 --> 00:16:22.000
Do you?

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:23.000
Well, we both know it wouldn't hurt him.

00:16:23.000 --> 00:16:24.000
You're a good man.

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:35.120
All right.

00:16:36.259 --> 00:16:37.059
What do you want?

00:16:37.259 --> 00:16:38.559
I just want Clark's help.

00:16:39.039 --> 00:16:39.700
With what?

00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:41.860
Look around you, Mr. Kent.

00:16:42.519 --> 00:16:43.240
You know what you see?

00:16:44.080 --> 00:16:45.639
The veneer of safety.

00:16:46.240 --> 00:16:48.299
Now, people like me are sworn to protect that.

00:16:48.600 --> 00:16:50.080
I'm the guy standing between the criminals

00:16:50.080 --> 00:16:51.679
and respectable citizens like yourself.

00:16:51.679 --> 00:16:56.719
Now, Clark has a gift,

00:16:57.639 --> 00:17:02.279
and I would like to use his talents to further my cause.

00:17:03.379 --> 00:17:06.299
I will not let you exploit my son.

00:17:09.359 --> 00:17:12.619
I've spent the morning going through the local police files.

00:17:14.200 --> 00:17:15.980
Clark's name comes up quite a bit.

00:17:17.220 --> 00:17:19.720
Clark has never been in trouble a day in his life, Phelan.

00:17:19.720 --> 00:17:20.519
No arrests.

00:17:20.519 --> 00:17:22.519
But he's been around a lot of crime scenes.

00:17:22.519 --> 00:17:25.519
Now, maybe that's coincidence.

00:17:25.519 --> 00:17:30.519
Or maybe it's just his natural instinct to get involved.

00:17:36.279 --> 00:17:39.279
Okay, I will give you whatever you want.

00:17:39.279 --> 00:17:42.279
You just stay away from my family.

00:17:46.279 --> 00:17:48.279
I want your son.

00:17:50.519 --> 00:17:51.099
No.

00:17:56.059 --> 00:17:57.059
I'll be in touch.

00:18:02.839 --> 00:18:04.480
Of course, if you don't agree,

00:18:05.059 --> 00:18:06.940
I will tell the world what I know.

00:18:07.960 --> 00:18:09.700
Best case, Clark's under a microscope.

00:18:10.139 --> 00:18:12.619
Worst case, he's a freak in a jar.

00:18:13.240 --> 00:18:16.059
Either way, his normal life is over.

00:18:16.059 --> 00:18:21.059
Well, you don't have to push me.

00:18:21.059 --> 00:18:23.579
Oh, easy there, Mr. Kent!

00:18:30.879 --> 00:18:31.779
We were just talking.

00:18:31.779 --> 00:18:37.740
Now if I were you, I'd learn to keep that temper in check.

00:18:37.740 --> 00:18:40.519
That could get you in a lot of trouble.

00:18:40.519 --> 00:18:42.019
I appreciate it.

00:18:42.019 --> 00:18:44.200
I appreciate the opportunity, sir.

00:18:45.279 --> 00:18:45.440
Oh, thank you.

00:18:45.460 --> 00:18:45.599
rehab 700-75.

00:18:45.599 --> 00:18:52.699
Hey, Clark.

00:18:53.959 --> 00:18:54.480
You okay?

00:18:55.539 --> 00:18:55.980
Fine.

00:18:56.599 --> 00:18:58.079
Just doing a little research.

00:18:58.559 --> 00:19:00.519
Have you heard anything about Lana's meeting with Kwan?

00:19:01.099 --> 00:19:02.059
Oh, I'm sure it'll work out.

00:19:02.699 --> 00:19:03.139
Hey.

00:19:04.319 --> 00:19:05.159
So how'd it go?

00:19:05.919 --> 00:19:07.500
Well, it's interesting.

00:19:08.539 --> 00:19:10.319
Bottom line it, when can we send out the next issue?

00:19:10.679 --> 00:19:11.480
The day after tomorrow.

00:19:12.399 --> 00:19:12.740
Cool.

00:19:12.740 --> 00:19:14.940
Except, uh...

00:19:14.940 --> 00:19:16.279
Um...

00:19:16.279 --> 00:19:17.259
Kwan made me the new editor.

00:19:22.000 --> 00:19:23.720
Okay, um...

00:19:23.720 --> 00:19:24.180
Rewind.

00:19:24.579 --> 00:19:26.240
I need you to say that last part, Ian.

00:19:26.779 --> 00:19:29.660
After I made my case, Kwan said that if I had that much passion,

00:19:29.859 --> 00:19:30.960
I should be in charge.

00:19:33.960 --> 00:19:35.400
I don't believe this.

00:19:35.599 --> 00:19:37.900
Chloe, it's the only way he'd reopen the paper.

00:19:38.120 --> 00:19:39.400
So what? Cheerleading's not enough?

00:19:40.099 --> 00:19:41.700
Maybe the editor of the school newspaper

00:19:41.700 --> 00:19:42.720
looks better on a college application.

00:19:42.740 --> 00:19:43.740
That isn't it.

00:19:43.740 --> 00:19:45.240
I just figured you could ghostwrite

00:19:45.240 --> 00:19:46.740
until we got you reinstated.

00:19:46.740 --> 00:19:48.240
Okay, so then I would work for you.

00:19:48.240 --> 00:19:49.740
The paper would still be yours.

00:19:49.740 --> 00:19:50.740
Wait, wait, wait.

00:19:50.740 --> 00:19:52.240
Chloe, think about it.

00:19:52.240 --> 00:19:53.240
It's not a bad idea.

00:19:55.240 --> 00:19:56.740
It figures you'd side with her.

00:19:56.740 --> 00:19:57.740
I'm not taking anyone's side.

00:19:57.740 --> 00:19:58.740
Yeah, right, Clark.

00:19:58.740 --> 00:20:00.740
You're completely objective in all things Lana.

00:20:03.740 --> 00:20:04.740
Gotta go.

00:20:04.740 --> 00:20:06.740
No, please, Clark. Stay.

00:20:06.740 --> 00:20:07.740
Take my desk.

00:20:07.740 --> 00:20:09.740
Chloe, this isn't what you think.

00:20:09.740 --> 00:20:10.740
You know what the weirdest part is?

00:20:10.740 --> 00:20:11.980
For a man like you,

00:20:11.980 --> 00:20:13.480
for a millisecond,

00:20:13.480 --> 00:20:14.980
I almost thought you were my friend.

00:20:30.980 --> 00:20:31.980
Get in, kid.

00:20:37.980 --> 00:20:38.980
What do you want, Phelan?

00:20:38.980 --> 00:20:40.480
Hey, your father came to see me.

00:20:40.480 --> 00:20:41.480
He seems like a really good man.

00:20:41.980 --> 00:20:43.480
Always putting his family first.

00:20:44.480 --> 00:20:46.480
Now, if I were you,

00:20:46.480 --> 00:20:47.980
I'd start thinking like him.

00:20:51.980 --> 00:20:53.480
I assume you've had a chance

00:20:53.480 --> 00:20:54.980
to read my father's proposal.

00:20:55.480 --> 00:20:56.480
I didn't have to.

00:20:56.980 --> 00:20:57.980
Oh.

00:20:58.480 --> 00:20:59.980
So you've added mind reading

00:20:59.980 --> 00:21:01.480
to your many abilities.

00:21:01.480 --> 00:21:02.980
I know why you're here, Victoria.

00:21:03.980 --> 00:21:05.980
Sir Harry wants to take over Luthor Corp,

00:21:05.980 --> 00:21:07.480
and he needs my shares to do it.

00:21:07.980 --> 00:21:10.980
Your father didn't dream up this little plan, did he?

00:21:10.980 --> 00:21:11.980
I know.

00:21:11.980 --> 00:21:12.980
He's just a...

00:21:12.980 --> 00:21:14.980
Do you think if you take over Luthor Corp,

00:21:14.980 --> 00:21:17.980
Daddy will finally give you the respect you deserve?

00:21:17.980 --> 00:21:19.980
He won't, Victoria.

00:21:19.980 --> 00:21:21.980
So what are you suggesting?

00:21:21.980 --> 00:21:24.980
You came to play on my hatred of my father.

00:21:24.980 --> 00:21:26.980
Now I'm gonna play on yours.

00:21:26.980 --> 00:21:28.980
Why take one company

00:21:28.980 --> 00:21:30.980
when you can take two?

00:21:30.980 --> 00:21:33.980
You know they'd probably kill us.

00:21:33.980 --> 00:21:34.980
Probably.

00:21:34.980 --> 00:21:37.980
But that's what makes life interesting.

00:21:37.980 --> 00:21:38.980
She's coming.

00:21:38.980 --> 00:21:39.980
She's coming.

00:21:39.980 --> 00:21:40.980
She's coming.

00:21:40.980 --> 00:21:41.980
She's coming.

00:22:04.980 --> 00:22:05.980
What are we doing here?

00:22:05.980 --> 00:22:08.980
You wanna know the biggest obstacle to my job, Clark?

00:22:08.980 --> 00:22:09.980
It's not the perps.

00:22:09.980 --> 00:22:11.980
It's the bureaucracy.

00:22:11.980 --> 00:22:13.980
I mean, how am I supposed to fight crime

00:22:13.980 --> 00:22:15.980
with one hand tied behind my back?

00:22:15.980 --> 00:22:17.980
I thought you said we were going after bad guys.

00:22:17.980 --> 00:22:18.980
Oh, we are.

00:22:18.980 --> 00:22:21.980
They're called internal affairs.

00:22:21.980 --> 00:22:24.980
In fact, the head of the IA division

00:22:24.980 --> 00:22:26.980
lives right up there on the fifth floor.

00:22:30.980 --> 00:22:32.980
I'm not gonna hurt anybody.

00:22:32.980 --> 00:22:33.980
Relax.

00:22:33.980 --> 00:22:35.980
You're just gonna help me retrieve some files.

00:22:35.980 --> 00:22:37.980
You see, these IA types,

00:22:37.980 --> 00:22:39.980
they have a real, uh, trust problem.

00:22:39.980 --> 00:22:41.980
Well, it turns out the deputy chief

00:22:41.980 --> 00:22:44.980
keeps all of his most sensitive case files at home.

00:22:44.980 --> 00:22:46.980
A man's got a safe.

00:22:46.980 --> 00:22:48.980
So you find it, you open it,

00:22:48.980 --> 00:22:51.980
and you bring me whatever's inside.

00:22:51.980 --> 00:22:53.980
You do this one thing for me,

00:22:53.980 --> 00:22:56.980
and I will never trouble you again.

00:22:56.980 --> 00:22:58.980
I know what you're about, Phelan.

00:22:58.980 --> 00:23:00.980
Lex Luthor told me.

00:23:00.980 --> 00:23:03.980
Well, your friend Lex

00:23:03.980 --> 00:23:06.980
isn't exactly on the side of the angels.

00:23:06.980 --> 00:23:08.980
He's got his secrets.

00:23:08.980 --> 00:23:10.980
Just like you.

00:23:10.980 --> 00:23:12.980
It's apartment 517.

00:23:38.980 --> 00:23:40.980
I'm gonna go find him.

00:23:40.980 --> 00:23:42.980
I'll be right back.

00:24:05.980 --> 00:24:07.980
Hey, Phelan!

00:24:08.980 --> 00:24:11.980
What'd you file?

00:24:11.980 --> 00:24:14.980
It's all yours.

00:24:16.980 --> 00:24:18.980
What'd you call that?

00:24:20.980 --> 00:24:22.980
You're making a big mistake.

00:24:38.980 --> 00:24:42.980
I'll call the police.

00:24:42.980 --> 00:24:44.980
Morning, guys.

00:24:44.980 --> 00:24:46.980
What time did you get in last night?

00:24:46.980 --> 00:24:48.980
I didn't hear you.

00:24:48.980 --> 00:24:49.980
Uh, late.

00:24:49.980 --> 00:24:51.980
I was helping Lana at the torch.

00:24:51.980 --> 00:24:54.980
I sort of lost track of time.

00:24:54.980 --> 00:24:56.980
Clark, has, um,

00:24:56.980 --> 00:24:58.980
has Phelan tried to contact you?

00:24:58.980 --> 00:24:59.980
Dad, don't worry.

00:24:59.980 --> 00:25:01.980
I think he's out of our lives forever.

00:25:01.980 --> 00:25:06.980
Ethan.

00:25:06.980 --> 00:25:08.980
Uh, what's going on?

00:25:08.980 --> 00:25:10.980
I got a warrant.

00:25:12.980 --> 00:25:14.980
It's a warrant to search your property, Jonathan.

00:25:14.980 --> 00:25:16.980
A warrant?

00:25:16.980 --> 00:25:18.980
Come on in.

00:25:18.980 --> 00:25:20.980
What for?

00:25:20.980 --> 00:25:23.980
I got a tip from Metropolis PD.

00:25:24.980 --> 00:25:27.980
You better come and take a look at this.

00:25:36.980 --> 00:25:39.980
Looks like he was shot in the heart.

00:25:42.980 --> 00:25:45.980
You want to explain to me what a dead body's doing in your barn, Jonathan?

00:25:45.980 --> 00:25:47.980
I have no idea. I've never seen that man before.

00:25:47.980 --> 00:25:48.980
Ethan.

00:25:48.980 --> 00:25:51.980
We found this hidden under the seat in the truck.

00:25:53.980 --> 00:25:56.980
That is not my gun, and I have no idea how it got in my truck.

00:25:56.980 --> 00:25:58.980
I'm sorry, Jonathan, but we're gonna have to place you under arrest.

00:25:58.980 --> 00:26:00.980
Dad.

00:26:00.980 --> 00:26:02.980
It's all right. Um...

00:26:02.980 --> 00:26:04.980
Call Bill Ross and have him meet me at the jail.

00:26:06.980 --> 00:26:08.980
You're not taking him!

00:26:08.980 --> 00:26:10.980
Clark. Clark.

00:26:10.980 --> 00:26:12.980
I need you to stay here.

00:26:12.980 --> 00:26:14.980
That...

00:26:14.980 --> 00:26:16.980
And I need you to be strong.

00:26:26.980 --> 00:26:28.980
I'll follow in the car.

00:26:28.980 --> 00:26:31.980
I'll follow in the car.

00:26:48.980 --> 00:26:51.980
That's what you get for trying to be a hero, Clark.

00:26:51.980 --> 00:26:54.980
You're a pretty smart boy, but you forget...

00:26:54.980 --> 00:26:57.980
I've been doing this a long time.

00:26:58.980 --> 00:26:59.980
Who's that man?

00:26:59.980 --> 00:27:02.980
Did you really think that you could double-cross me?

00:27:02.980 --> 00:27:06.980
Clark, my job is about scenarios.

00:27:06.980 --> 00:27:08.980
You never enter a crack house with one plan.

00:27:08.980 --> 00:27:11.980
You go in with ten. That's how you survive.

00:27:12.980 --> 00:27:14.980
The truth is, kid,

00:27:14.980 --> 00:27:17.980
you didn't leave me with a lot of options!

00:27:17.980 --> 00:27:18.980
I want my dad out of jail.

00:27:18.980 --> 00:27:21.980
You complicate my life, I'm gonna complicate yours.

00:27:22.980 --> 00:27:24.980
Call him now! Tell him what you did!

00:27:26.980 --> 00:27:27.980
What is it, Clark?

00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:29.980
You want to kill me?

00:27:29.980 --> 00:27:32.980
You think that's the answer to your problems?

00:27:32.980 --> 00:27:34.980
I want him out!

00:27:34.980 --> 00:27:36.980
Well, then we both want something.

00:27:36.980 --> 00:27:38.980
Only you...

00:27:38.980 --> 00:27:40.980
have a lot more to lose.

00:27:48.980 --> 00:27:52.980
I don't want any more surprises.

00:27:52.980 --> 00:27:55.980
I'm gonna let you think about last night.

00:27:58.980 --> 00:27:59.980
Just you and me, and the rest of us.

00:27:59.980 --> 00:28:01.980
I'm gonna let you drink the كکrap the time you have.

00:28:01.980 --> 00:28:03.980
I want to really cheating for you and our bulbs.

00:28:03.980 --> 00:28:05.980
We'll admit it...

00:28:05.980 --> 00:28:06.980
that we're even.

00:28:10.980 --> 00:28:11.980
Abbott, please.

00:28:11.980 --> 00:28:26.779
Don't you ever call me

00:28:26.779 --> 00:28:30.440
I heard about your dad.

00:28:31.279 --> 00:28:32.259
I know it isn't true.

00:28:34.460 --> 00:28:34.819
Thanks.

00:28:38.359 --> 00:28:39.019
How you doing?

00:28:39.920 --> 00:28:42.619
To be honest, I'm in way over my head.

00:28:43.680 --> 00:28:45.200
All I wanted to do was help Chloe out,

00:28:45.259 --> 00:28:47.339
and now I feel like I've completely screwed up everything.

00:28:49.500 --> 00:28:51.539
Guess that's what you get when you try to be a hero.

00:28:53.899 --> 00:28:54.740
I know the feeling.

00:28:56.779 --> 00:29:01.519
You ever think your aunt's life would be simpler if she hadn't adopted you?

00:29:02.859 --> 00:29:03.799
Look what's going on.

00:29:07.160 --> 00:29:10.180
It just seems like all I ever do is complicate my parents' lives.

00:29:11.599 --> 00:29:14.039
You can't blame yourself for what's happening with your dad.

00:29:15.720 --> 00:29:17.420
Every family goes through rough times.

00:29:18.319 --> 00:29:20.680
When I was ten, I tried to run away to Metropolis.

00:29:21.759 --> 00:29:24.039
Nell found me at the bus stop. It was freezing.

00:29:24.940 --> 00:29:26.099
As she was driving me home,

00:29:26.180 --> 00:29:26.759
I asked her if she could help me.

00:29:26.779 --> 00:29:28.000
She said she regretted adopting me.

00:29:29.079 --> 00:29:30.200
She stopped the car.

00:29:30.819 --> 00:29:32.119
I remember because it started snowing.

00:29:32.920 --> 00:29:34.019
She looked me in the eye.

00:29:35.859 --> 00:29:37.700
She said it was the best thing she had ever done.

00:29:39.319 --> 00:29:41.759
She didn't love me any less because I was adopted.

00:29:43.279 --> 00:29:45.000
But she worried about me more.

00:29:49.420 --> 00:29:50.160
I'm gonna go.

00:29:52.559 --> 00:29:53.460
Don't worry, Clark.

00:29:55.099 --> 00:29:56.160
It'll all work out.

00:29:56.759 --> 00:29:58.460
Then I'll really have to choose my future.

00:29:59.759 --> 00:30:01.160
That's what I said, don't you ever.

00:30:01.940 --> 00:30:02.940
We're buying allies.

00:30:05.940 --> 00:30:07.099
Dude, no.

00:30:10.039 --> 00:30:11.619
What are you talking about?

00:30:13.519 --> 00:30:15.599
We were talking about her, and you were saying we had a baby.

00:30:16.940 --> 00:30:18.460
You guys were looking-

00:30:21.700 --> 00:30:22.960
Me?

00:30:23.339 --> 00:30:25.799
Stop talking and forget all that.

00:30:25.799 --> 00:30:26.419
Where's your mother?

00:30:26.940 --> 00:30:27.899
Police are questioning her.

00:30:31.839 --> 00:30:32.839
I lied to you.

00:30:35.019 --> 00:30:35.759
What do you mean?

00:30:36.579 --> 00:30:38.119
I did see Phelan again.

00:30:43.419 --> 00:30:43.819
When?

00:30:45.240 --> 00:30:45.879
Last night.

00:30:46.639 --> 00:30:48.240
I went with him to Metropolis.

00:30:48.700 --> 00:30:49.579
Broke into an apartment.

00:30:50.919 --> 00:30:52.779
Found a safe with confidential files.

00:30:53.619 --> 00:30:54.339
Oh, Clark.

00:30:54.339 --> 00:30:55.879
I didn't have a choice.

00:30:56.240 --> 00:30:57.939
Well, I'm sure that's what he wanted you to think,

00:30:58.000 --> 00:30:59.539
but you always have a choice, son.

00:30:59.679 --> 00:31:01.220
I was protecting you and Mom.

00:31:01.359 --> 00:31:03.819
You cannot protect your mother and I by lying to us.

00:31:03.879 --> 00:31:04.339
Come on.

00:31:07.899 --> 00:31:08.839
Dad, there's more.

00:31:11.299 --> 00:31:14.139
Phelan came back after you were arrested.

00:31:15.039 --> 00:31:18.579
He got so angry that I grabbed him.

00:31:19.199 --> 00:31:21.059
And for a second, I wanted to...

00:31:24.339 --> 00:31:26.679
I wanted to kill him.

00:31:29.699 --> 00:31:30.919
But you didn't, right?

00:31:31.919 --> 00:31:33.799
Yeah, but I was close.

00:31:44.480 --> 00:31:47.599
Believe me, son, I know all there is to know about losing your temper.

00:31:48.379 --> 00:31:50.279
But you can't afford to do it.

00:31:51.339 --> 00:31:52.819
This is Phelan's game.

00:31:53.359 --> 00:31:54.319
And he will play you.

